          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1709818965823-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>pepper strips </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste </strong>and <strong>fish sauce </strong>in a bowl with the juice of <strong>half </strong>the <strong>lime[s]</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water </strong>– this is your <strong>pad Thai sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1709818969594-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1709818969594-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1709818969594-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1709818969594-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1709818969594-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with your <strong>ginger paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, push the chicken and pepper to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the other side</p><p>Stir the<strong> egg[s]</strong> with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1709818973252-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1709818973252-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1709818973252-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1709818973252-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1709818973252-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once scrambled, add the <strong>drained rice noodles </strong>and <strong>pad Thai sauce </strong>to the pan, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your<strong> chicken pad Thai noodles</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1709818977000-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
